The paper proposes a new model for kernel online learning that encourages sparsity while maintaining performance. This is a problem that is relevant to several sub-fields of computer science, including machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computer vision (cs.CV), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), and social and information networks (cs.SI). However, given that the paper focuses on developing a new model for online learning, cs.LG and cs.AI are the most likely sub-categories.
